race.comment: LADY LUPARA (5) turned things around last start and landed the prize after being in contention on the corner over this track and trip. No reason she cannot salute again. GREATESTOFEASE (3) was prominent at the bend and progressed nicely last start to finish a close second over 1900m at Oakbank. Best figures measure up. Sure to run well. GRINZINGER ALLEE (8) had their measure last start when scoring by a head but does lug more weight this time. WARRANDYTE ROAD (6) registered a strong win two runs ago then turned in a decent effort last time out when fourth at Strathalbyn. Ticking along nicely and should be very competitive again.
